						<summary>

						<p>Pillar lying infront of the Madanagōpālaśvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1199</hi> and other details are not known. It may be correspond to 1277 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to be a grant of land by Pubbaya of Niravadyaprōlu to Dēvebōya for ghee for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva, stipulating an annual payment of one <hi rend="italic">Vaṁśavarddhana gadya</hi> and two <hi rend="italic">chinnas,</hi> probably as interest by the done.</p>						

						</summary>
